President Obama has announced his intent to nominate three individuals for key administration posts. Caryn A. Wagner is nominated for Under Secretary for Intelligence and Analysis at the Department of Homeland Security. She has a background in intelligence resource management and has served in various positions in the intelligence community. Philip S. Goldberg is nominated for Assistant Secretary, Bureau of Intelligence and Research at the Department of State. He is currently the United States Coordinator for Implementation of United Nations Security Council Resolutions on North Korea. P. David Lopez is nominated for General Counsel at the Equal Employment Opportunity Commission. He has been with the EEOC for 13 years and has a background in employment litigation.